### FINDING: Server Version Disclosure via X-Powered-By Header  
SEVERITY: Low  
EVIDENCE: `X-Powered-By: PHP/8.5.4`  
DESCRIPTION: The server reveals its PHP version through the `X-Powered-By` header, providing attackers with version information that could be used to target known vulnerabilities.  
IMPACT: Enables attackers to tailor exploits based on the disclosed version.  
RECOMMENDATION: Disable or hide the `X-Powered-By` header in Apache (e.g., `Header unset X-Powered-By` or `ServerTokens Prod`/`ServerSignature Off`).  
CVSS: 3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:N (score 0.0)  
CWE: CWE‑200  
OWASP: A6:2021 Security Misconfiguration  

### FINDING: Insecure HTTP (No TLS)  
SEVERITY: Medium  
EVIDENCE: `http://192.168.1.49:4280`  
DESCRIPTION: The application is served over plain HTTP, exposing all traffic—including credentials and session cookies—to eavesdropping and man‑in‑the‑middle attacks.  
IMPACT: Credentials and session data can be intercepted, leading to account compromise.  
RECOMMENDATION: Deploy TLS/SSL, redirect HTTP to HTTPS, and enforce HSTS.  
CVSS: 3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:N/A:N (score 6.5)  
